<p>Say I have this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;  This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;This is another paragraph.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want it to be:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is another paragraph.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I cannot simply use <code>trim()</code> as there is the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> at the beginning. But I also can't use the <code>str_replace()</code>/<code>preg_replace()</code> as I need to retain the empty space inside <code>This is a paragraph</code>. How should I achieve this? Thanks!</p>